Length 0.70–72 mm . Colour dark reddish brown, sparsely pubescent, smooth and shining, legs and antennae uniformly dusky yellow. Antennomeres 1,2 large, 3 attenuated, 4 almost parallel sided, 5–9 rounded, 10 almost spherical, 11 slightly elongate, both 10 and 11 bearing visible sensillae and together forming a club, (
Fig. 28
). Head broad, with large, shallow, setae bearing pits on the vertex and a transverse sulcate groove behind eyes not bridged laterally from eye to temple, ventral interruption approximately 1 / 3 width of the head. Pronotum 0.18 mm long and 0.23–0.24 mm wide, with two longitudinal furrows on each side adjacent to midline and not shorter than 90 % of pronotal length, flanked laterally by a single basal depression; posterior edge with a rounded emargination fringed by hairs in front of scutellum. Scutellum with a central longitudinal keel separating two large circular foveae at base and two smaller, deeper foveae at the anterior angles. Wings present of usual Ptiliid form. Elytra 0.42–0.43 mm long, 0.27–0.28 mm wide, with a shallow depression at the humerus delimited laterally by a short carina. Mesoventrite with front angles strongly toothed. Abdominal ventrite VIII with two large circular foveae at lateral margins.
